Today I delivered the shirts for my donation project for the amazing kids at Ridgeline Pediatric. There’s too many shirts for a single post so look for more posts to come to see the all the shirts that were donated. 
Finally want to bring attention to children and families in your community. Across the world families are struggling to care for there children with rare and catastrophic disease. I am part one of those families. My son suffers from a rare form of catastrophic called Lennox Gastaut Syndrome and we rely on our community at times to get the simplest of tasks completed, like grocery shopping, getting kids to school etc. If you get anything from this post please get that these families are in your neighborhood, look for opportunities to help, you have no idea how much it will mean to these families. ❤️💜❤️ Hug your family, enjoy your day. You never know how many we will get together. 
Thank you!

More on my son’s story:

The newest addition to my glass collection- Amphora made by Maestro @cesaretoffolo 🙌🏼 some of my first exposures to flameworked glass consisted of staying up late with my brother, @itsbeaker, and watching film demonstrations of Cesare making immaculate goblets with his line tubing and gold leaf. It felt so fulfilling to travel to Murano (Glass Mecca) and hand-pick a piece of his to bring home. I will always remember and cherish this pilgrimage. Thank you, Cesare, for your hard work and dedication to the craft, and thank you, Ryan, for exposing me to the world of flame working. 'Flower of Life' - Freehand Woodburning on 5.5" x 11" Cedar Plank •••
Attempting to tackle a new medium can sometimes be a difficult task & I have always struggled with trying out new things; boy was I surprised when this piece started to manifest itself. Although the #woodburning process is different than what I'm used to, the sweet aroma of burnt Cedar kept beckoning me to work later into the night as I found myself in a peaceful state of being for the entire time I was creating. I'm very pleased  with how this one turned out, which almost never happens on my first try. Overall, I thoroughly enjoyed my 1st experience with this medium & I look forward to exploring my new form of meditation. 👁🧠💚
